The paper deals with properties of triangulations and paths in computational geometry, which suggests that cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The use of the term "spanning trees" suggests that cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) may also be relevant. The paper also discusses the potential application of the results to edge-unfolding of polyhedral convex caps, which could fall under cs.GR (Graphics) or cs.SI (Sound and Image Processing). Finally, the paper involves some conjectures, which could potentially involve cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
